# Microsoft 365 / Office 365 Setup (GoDaddy):
# 1. Use your full Microsoft 365 email as SMTP_USERNAME
# 2. Use your Microsoft 365 account password as SMTP_PASSWORD
# 3. Make sure SMTP is enabled in your Microsoft 365 admin settings
# 4. Server: smtp.office365.com, Port: 587 (TLS/STARTTLS)
#
# For security, consider creating an App Password if available:
# - Sign in to your Microsoft account
# - Go to Security settings
# - Create an App Password for "Mail"

# Alternative SMTP Services:
# 
# Gmail:
# SMTP_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password-here
#
# Gmail App Password Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/security
# 2. Enable 2-Step Verification if not already enabled
# 3. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 4. Create a new app password for "Mail"
# 5. Use the 16-character password as SMTP_PASSWORD
#
# SendGrid: smtp.sendgrid.net (port 587)
# Mailgun: smtp.mailgun.org (port 587)
# AWS SES: email-smtp.region.amazonaws.com (port 587)
